          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1662456412920-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> – this is your<strong> dressed salad</strong></p><p>Once the fish is cooked, stir through the <strong>drained gnocchi </strong>until everything is fully combined and the gnocchi is warmed through – this is your <strong>tomato haddock gnocchi</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy cooking water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1662456427324-x200.jpg",
